\details{
The chain runs in order: stage-1 input (ebrecipe seam) -> beta-GMM precision seam
-> native deconvolution -> posterior weights -> one-level posterior ->
\code{\link[=gp_pairwise]{gp_pairwise()}} -> \code{\link[=gp_grade_path]{gp_grade_path()}} -> \code{\link[=gp_select_grade]{gp_select_grade()}} -> \code{\link[=gp_report_card]{gp_report_card()}}.
Grade labels are integers in \verb{\{1, ..., n\}} and carry no ranking-superiority
statement of any kind. Solver honesty: a gurobi solve that stops at a gap or time
limit keeps that status (surfaced as an \code{UNVERIFIED} producer status);
\code{acceptance_mode = TRUE} only adds optimization attempts, never a relabel.
